  <static seed="1408" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalExpressionAlgebraSkills/addSubtractRationalExpressions100.pg">
    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{-\frac{6t}{t^{2}-9}+\frac{t}{t-3}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{t}{t+3}, t\ne 3</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {-\frac{6t}{t^{2}-9}+\frac{t}{t-3}} 
      \amp = {-\frac{6t}{\left(t-3\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+3\right)}+\frac{t}{t-3}} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{6t}{\left(t-3\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+3\right)}+\frac{t}{t-3}} \cdot \frac{(t+3)}{(t+3)} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{6t}{\left(t-3\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+3\right)}+\frac{t\mathopen{}\left(t+3\right)}{\left(t-3\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+3\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{-6t+t\mathopen{}\left(t+3\right)}{\left(t-3\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+3\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{-6t+t^{2}+3t}{\left(t-3\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+3\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{t^{2}-3t}{\left(t-3\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+3\right)}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{t\mathopen{}\left(t-3\right)}}{{\left(t-3\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+3\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{t}{t+3}, t\ne 3}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>t - 3</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>t \ne {3}</m>.</p>
</solution>
